1. Initialize a min-heap and insert the first element with its coordinates (0, 0).
2. Keep a visited set or 2D boolean array to remember which elements have been inserted into the min-heap. Set the element (0, 0) as visited.
3. Using a loop, pop the smallest element along with its coordinates from the min-heap and increment a counter.
4. If the counter reached k, then return the popped sum.
5. Add the element right below the current element if it is still inside the matrix and is not visited.
6. Add the element right to the current element if it is still inside the matrix and is not visited.
7. During each addition of a new cell, update the visited set or array and add the new sum (subtract the previous matrix element and add the new one) along with its coordinates to the heap.

